Terms: Licensed under GPLv3, but with the GCC Runtime Library Exception 3.1. This explicitly allows you to link this code into your independent (even closed-source) applications without triggering the copyleft requirements of the GPLv3.


Critical Isolation Note:
Kernel (Ring0) and userspace (Ring3) run in separate virtual address spaces and communicate only via syscall instructions. No static/dynamic linking exists between them.
Per FSF licensing guidance, userspace MIT code is not considered derivative work of the GPL kernel, and no copyleft infection occurs.

This repository complies with the REUSE Specification 3.3.
Each source file carries a matching SPDX license identifier.
